# Privacy & data governance

## Third parties

- AdSense / GA only when `import.meta.env.PROD`
- IDs via `PUBLIC_ADSENSE_ID` / `PUBLIC_GA_ID` (public) — never private keys
- Per-page: frontmatter `ads: false`
- Giscus: change repo/category only with intent; comments are third-party hosted

## User data (tools / AI)

Default posture for all tools (PDF, media, ASR, minutes, LocalAI):

| Data | Rule |
|------|------|
| Files / audio / transcripts | Stay in-browser; no silent upload |
| Cloud API (optional) | Explicit opt-in UI + user-supplied key in memory/`localStorage` only if requested; document risk |
| Analytics | Never send content of files/transcripts |
| Export | User-initiated download/copy only |
| Retention | Prefer session memory; clearable IndexedDB/Cache; document what persists |

## PII in meeting minutes / STT

- Treat transcripts as **sensitive**: names, employers, decisions, action items
- Label AI-generated minutes; allow edit before export
- Do not include raw audio/transcript in error reports, Giscus, or GA events
- Update `/privacy_policy/` when adding cloud STT or persistent storage of transcripts

## SVG / HTML

- `dangerouslyProcessSVG: true` is for **repo-managed** assets only
- Never process untrusted user SVG as Astro images without sanitization
